name: PG MOHD NASIR
bio: [('Beginning', 'He took up equestrian in 1999 and began riding competitively in 2005. (bt.com.bn, 15 Aug 2014)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at 2018 Asian Games in Indonesia. (borneobulletin.com.bn, 15 Feb 2018)'), ('Memorable', 'Winning a bronze medal at the 2017 South East Asian Games in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. (borneobulletin.com.bn, 15 Feb 2018)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralNATIONAL FIRSTHe became the first Bruneian rider to win a gold medal at a Competition Showjumping International [CSI] in Europe after claiming victory at the 2015 event in Oliva, Spain. He also became the first rider from the country to win an equestrian jumping medal at the South East Asian Games, claiming bronze at the 2017 Games in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. He had originally finished in fourth place, but Filipino rider Colin Syquia was stripped of his gold medal in February 2018 after his horse was found to have tested positive for a prohibited substance. (borneobulletin.com.bn, 15 Feb 2018, 12 Feb 2015)ABSENT IN INCHEONHe was unable to compete at the 2014 Asian Games in Incheon, Republic of Korea, following a dispute between him and the Brunei Darussalam National Olympic Council [BDNOC] over his eligibility to compete at the Games. The dispute arose after his athlete fitness test report was submitted after the closing date of the period of registration set by the Games organising committee, which resulted in the BDNOC stating that his registration could not be submitted. He attempted to appeal to the Court of Arbitration for Sport [CAS], but his application for an appeal was dismissed. (tas-cas.org, 10 Sep 2014) '), ('Relatives', 'His brother has represented Brunei Darussalam in equestrian. (bt.com.bn, 23 Aug 2009)'), ('Education', 'Business, Management - Brunel University , London, ENG'), ('Languages', 'English'), ('Highlights', 'RankEventYearLocationAsian GamesDSQJumping Individual2010Guangzhou, CHNSouth East Asian Games4Jumping Individual2017Kuala Lumpur, MAS8Jumping Individual2015Singapore, SIN')]
